Opgave A

A.1

Vi har:

\[ V_{in} = \text{DC} \quad Gain = 7 \quad z_1 = -1 \quad p_1 = -2 + 2 j \quad p_2 = -2 - 2j\]

Derfor: \[ H(s) = K \cdot \frac{s+1}{(s+2+2j)(s+2-2j)} \]

Omskriv til frekvensdomæne: \[ s = \omega j \qquad \omega = 0 \; \text{for DC}\]

Hvorfor: \[H(0) = K \cdot \frac{0+1}{(0+2+2j)(0+2-2j)} = 7 \] \[H(0) = \frac{K}{(2+2j)(2-2j)} = 7 \] \[H(0) = \frac{K}{4-4j+4j+4} = 7 \] \[H(0) = \frac{K}{8} = 7 \] \[K = 7 \cdot 8 \] \[K = 56 \]

Dermed:

\[\boxed{ H(s) = \frac{56(s+1)}{(s+2+2j)(s+2-2j)} }\]

Bodeplot der viser \(|H(s)|\) og \(\mathrm{arg}(H(s))\):

Stepsvar:

\[ \frac{1}{s}\cdot H(s) \]

A.2

Vi har:

\[ V_{in} = \text{DC} \quad Gain = 3 \quad p_1 = -3 \quad p_2 = -2 \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = K \cdot \frac{1}{(s+3)(s+2)} \]

Omskriv til frekvensdomæne: \[ s = \omega j \qquad \omega = 0 \; \text{for DC}\]

Hvorfor: \[ K \frac{1}{(0+3)(0+2)} = 3 \] \[\frac{K}{6} = 3 \] \[K = 18 \]

Dermed:

\[ \boxed{ H(s) = \frac{18}{(s+3)(s+2)}} \]

Step plot:

\[ (-9\cdot e^{-2\cdot t }+6\cdot e^{-3\cdot t}+3) \]

A.3

Vi har :

\[ V_{in} = \text{DC} \quad Gain = -3 \]

\[ p_1 = -5+j \quad p_2 = -5-j \quad p_3 = -1+j \quad p_4 = -1-j \quad p_5 = -1 \]

Dermed:

\[ H(s) = \frac{K}{(s+5+j)(s+5-j)(s+1+j)(s+1-j)(s+1)} \]

Omskriv til frekvensdomæne: \[ s = \omega j \qquad \omega = 0 \; \text{for DC}\]

\[ H(0) = \frac{K}{(0+5+j)(0+5-j)(0+1+j)(0+1-j)(0+1)} = -3\] \[ H(0) = \frac{K}{(5+j)(5-j)(1+j)(1-j) \cdot 1} = -3 \] \[ H(0) = \frac{K}{52} = -3 \] \[ K = -3 \cdot 52 \] \[ K = -156 \]

Derfor:

\[ \boxed{ H(s) = \frac{-156}{(s+5+j)(s+5-j)(s+1+j)(s+1-j)(s+1)} } \]

\[ \boxed{ H(s) = \frac{-156}{s^5+13s^4+60s^3+120s^2+124s+52} } \]

A.4

Vi har :

\[ V_{in} = \text{DC} \quad Gain = 2 \]

\[ z_1 = -1 \quad z_2 = 2 \quad p_1 = -5 \quad p_2 = -2 \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = K \frac{(s+1)(s-2)}{(s+5)(s+2)} \]

Omskriv til frekvensdomæne: \[ s = \omega j \qquad \omega = 0 \; \text{for DC}\]

\[ H(s) = K \frac{(0+1)(0-2)}{(0+5)(0+2)} = 2 \]

\[ \frac{K}{10} = -1 \]

\[ K = -10 \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = -10 \frac{(s+1)(s-2)}{(s+5)(s+2)} \]

A.5

Vi har :

\[ V_{in} = \text{DC} \quad Gain = 1 \]

\[ z_1 = -1 \quad z_2 = 2 \quad p_1 = -5+j \quad p_2 = -5-j \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = K \frac{(s+1)}{(s+5-j)(s+5+j)} \]

Omskriv til frekvensdomæne: \[ s = \omega j \qquad \omega = 0 \; \text{for DC}\]

\[ H(s) = K \frac{(1)}{(5-j)(5+j)} = 1 \]

\[ K = 26 \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = 26 \frac{(s+1)}{(s+5-j)(s+5+j)} \]

A.6

Vi har :

\[ H(0) = 7 \]

\[ p_1 = -2 \quad p_2 = -1 \quad p_3 = 0 \]

Derfor:

\[ \]

Givet: \[ \lim_{s \to 0} H(s) = 7\] \[ \lim_{s \to 0} K \frac{1}{s^3+3s^2+2s} = 7\] \[ K = 14\] Derfor: \[ H(s) = \frac{14}{(s+2)(s+1)\cdot s} \]

Step plot: \[ -14\cdot e^{-t}+7\cdot e^{-2\cdot t}+7 \]

A.7

Vi har :

\[ H(0) = 2 \]

\[ z_0 = -5 \quad z_1 = 2 \quad p_1 = 0 \quad p_2 = -2+2j \quad p_3 = -2-2j \]

Derfor:

\[ H(s) = K \cdot \frac{(s+5)(s-2)}{s(s+2-2j)(s+2+2j)} \]

Med slutværdien indsat:

\[ \lim_{s \to 0} s H(s) = 2 \]

\[ \lim_{s \to 0} s K \cdot \frac{(s+5)(s-2)}{s(s+2-2j)(s+2+2j)} = 2 \]

Dette giver:

\[ K = \frac{-8}{5} \]

Hvorfor:

\[ H(s) = \frac{-8}{5} \cdot \frac{(s+5)(s-2)}{s(s+2-2j)(s+2+2j)} \]

Opgave C

C.1

Graf givet:

Funktion der er plottet er : \[f(t) = e^{-\frac{1}{2} t} u(t) \]

Det giver den invLP: \[\mathcal{L}^{-1} \{f(t)\} \quad F(s) = \frac{2}{2s+1} \] Som har polen: \(p_1 = -\frac{1}{2}\)

C.2

Graf givet:

Funktion der er plottet er : \[f(t) =\sin(t) u(t) \]

Det giver den invLP: \[\mathcal{L}^{-1} \{f(t)\} \quad F(s) = \frac{1}{s^2+1^2} \] Som har polerne: \(p = \pm j\)

C.3

Graf givet:

Funktion der er plottet er : \[f(t) =e^{-0.5t} \sin(t) u(t) \]

Det giver den invLP: \[\mathcal{L}^{-1} \{f(t)\} \quad F(s) = \frac{4}{4s^2+4s+5}\] \[ 4\frac{1}{4s^2+4s+5}\] Dette giver polerne: \[ P = -\frac{1}{2} \pm j \]

Det giver den invLP: \[\mathcal{L}^{-1} \{f(t)\} \quad F(s) = \frac{4}{4s^2+4s+5}\] \[ 4\frac{1}{4s^2+4s+5}\] Dette giver polerne: \[ P = -\frac{1}{2} \pm j \]
